KABUL, Nov. 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 worshippers were injured as a blast rocked a mosque in Achin district of Afghanistan's eastern Nangarhar province on Friday, an eyewitness said. The blast, according to the eyewitness who declined to be named, took place at 01:30 p.m. local time Friday when the mosque was full of worshippers. However, locals believed that the number of casualties could be higher. This is the second blast inside a mosque in the eastern Nangarhar province over the past month. The hardliner Islamic State outfit had claimed responsibility for the previous blast. Enditem